  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "Before the Prophet Muhammad, the term \"Islam\" as a religious identity did not exist as it does today. However, the concept of \"Islam,\" which means \"submission\" or \"surrender\" to the will of God, is considered by Muslims to be the essence of the faith that was revealed to all prophets throughout history. The Quran teaches that individuals like Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus were also submitters to God and practiced a form of Islam in this broader sense.\n\nIn a more specific historical and doctrinal context, the religion that we now recognize as Islam was formally established with the teachings of Muhammad in the early 7th century CE. Muhammad is regarded by Muslims as the last prophet in a long line of prophets and the one who completed the revelation of God's message, which is articulated in the Quran.\n\nSo, while the foundational idea of submission to God existed and was practiced long before Muhammad, the formal and organized religion of Islam as it is understood today began with him.",
